ce:section.ce:para:
With the increase of the types and concentrations of pollutants in environment, people gradually realize the seriousness of environmental pollution. Hazardous substances remaining in the environment are a major threat to human health. For example, p-AZO as one of azo dyes is widely used in various industrial fields. It can enter soil and water due to the discharge of crop-spraying pesticide or cosmetics, rubber, paper, plastic and textile polluted wastewater (Aljerf, 2018). Although it exists at trace concentrations in water due to its strong lipophilicity, which is easily enriched in organisms, leading to the increase of the concentration hundreds of times, or even higher and resulting in irreversible accumulation of toxicity to the human body (
                     Hlongwane et al., 2019; Suzuki et al., 2020; Zhou et al., 2019
                     ). It has been proven to be one of the culprits for cancer. Therefore, it is very indispensable to establish convenient and rapid analytical methods.
